{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/web-based-infographic-vector-editor/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Mark Vital - software developer and information designer"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"b9d10855-07ec-5472-bf8f-41dbc865ecc2","excerpt":"I build a proof-of concept of web-based vector editor to build infographics for Adioma 2.0. All the geometry is rendered using in-browser SVG capabilities. The…","html":"<p>I build a proof-of concept of web-based vector editor to build infographics for Adioma 2.0. All the geometry is rendered using in-browser SVG capabilities. The editor is using React.js to Manipulate SVG and React hooks as state management. \nIt supports selecting and manipulation with multiple objects, multi-line formatted text, inserting icons and illustrations.\nThe documents are stored in MongoDB database on backend.\nThe users, authentification system is implemented using JSON-web token.\nThe backend is managed with ReactAdmin.</p>\n<p><em>Tech</em>: React, Node.js, MongoDB, SVG, ReactAdmin</p>\n<p>Scope: development</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Web-based Infographic Vector Editor","date":"January 28, 2021","description":null,"items":[{"title":"Editor Screen","image":"the-editor.jpg"},{"title":"The Dashboard of User Graphics","image":"user-graphics-dashboard.jpg"},{"title":"Admin Panel","image":"admin-panel.jpg"}],"coverImage":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fullWidth","backgroundColor":"#f8f8f8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/0b49bfa5e7418e05c1ed3c821c80ce2c/231aa/cover.jpg","srcSet":"/static/0b49bfa5e7418e05c1ed3c821c80ce2c/5f965/cover.jpg 750w,\n/static/0b49bfa5e7418e05c1ed3c821c80ce2c/76f9a/cover.jpg 1080w,\n/static/0b49bfa5e7418e05c1ed3c821c80ce2c/54fb8/cover.jpg 1366w,\n/static/0b49bfa5e7418e05c1ed3c821c80ce2c/231aa/cover.jpg 1400w","sizes":"100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/0b49bfa5e7418e05c1ed3c821c80ce2c/ee7ce/cover.webp 750w,\n/static/0b49bfa5e7418e05c1ed3c821c80ce2c/